<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>361310</id>
	<title>Firefox doesn't display an image if the images size isn't correctly stated in the html</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9a1) Gecko/20061119 Minefield/3.0a1
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9a1) Gecko/20061119 Minefield/3.0a1</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">If a web page incorrectly reports the size of an image then firefox won't display the image correctly, instead it displays some other recently viewed image.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">For example, on the page http://www.sasi.group.shef.ac.uk/worldmapper/display.php?selected=227 the map of HIV prevalence is reported in the code as height='256' when in fact the image is 252 pixels high.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">Firefox should automatically resize the image.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">Here's another page that's completely fubar http://medicine.ucsd.edu/clinicalmed/head.htm</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
